Dutt's first film after his 1993 arrest was Daud (1997). It did average business at the box office despite of getting a lot of publicity. This was followed by Dushman which did well financially. 1999 was an excellent year for Dutt and one that is regarded as his comeback, with all of his five releases being amongst the highest-grossing films of that year. He began it by starring in the Mahesh Bhatt-directed hit film Kartoos, followed by Khoobsurat, Haseena Maan Jaayegi, Daag: The Fire and Vaasta
